    "The strongest case against this proposal is not that Marcellus is the wrong product; it is that the ticket has been sized against product attractiveness rather than against the architecture the household has already committed to in its stated mandate. Three G1 bands print at or beyond boundary simultaneously: equity at 71.7 percent against a 70 percent ceiling, debt at 13.3 percent against a 20 percent floor, and a 16.7 percent single-position concentration against a 15 percent standard ceiling. A proposal that disturbs one band at the boundary is a clarification; a proposal that disturbs three bands at the boundary in a single action is a structural signature, and the signature here is that the Rs 3 Cr figure was anchored on the FD reserve available rather than on the headroom the mandate could absorb. S1's counterfactual at Rs 2.0-2.2 Cr is not a marginal alternative; it is the sizing the architecture would have produced if the architecture had been the starting point.",
